The author extends Christmas greetings to Orthodox Christians around the world, acknowledging their resilience and love for their communities during difficult times. They express condolences to those who have lost loved ones during the pandemic, and offer prayers for strength and purpose to those who are struggling. The author also highlights the ongoing persecution and discrimination faced by Orthodox Christians globally, reaffirming their commitment to religious freedom. They emphasize the message of Christmas, which is the promise of light in the darkness, and join Orthodox Christians in giving thanks and praying for peace, justice, freedom, and healing in the coming year.